main event: A civilian observed a white streak moving through the sky in Scullville, New Jersey, on January 27, 1950.
interesting points: The sighting lasted approximately 30 minutes,The object was noted to ascend at a 60-degree angle,The witness described the object as moving in a zigzag motion,The object eventually disappeared into a fog bank,There were no photographs or further technical data to support a comprehensive investigation.
sighted object: a white streak in the sky
witness description: a civilian from Scullville, New Jersey
